  prepared_dataset.sql.j2
  -----------------------
  The full pipeline query: assembles the three CTEs into a single
  CREATE TABLE AS SELECT that writes the analysis-ready dataset into
  the client's warehouse under the Argenta output schema.

  The resulting table has one row per user with:
    - user_id          — user identifier
    - variant          — 'control' or 'treatment'
    - metric_*         — aggregated outcome values per configured event
    - feature columns  — user attributes for CUPED and (Phase 2) CATE

  This table is the input to the Python stats layer.  It stays in the
  client's warehouse — Argenta never moves it externally.

  Template variables (all pre-computed by SQLPipelineGenerator):
    ctas_statement       — CREATE OR REPLACE TABLE / DROP + CREATE
                           (dialect-specific, built by dialect.create_table_as)
    exposure_dedup_cte   — rendered exposure_dedup.sql.j2 block
    outcome_join_cte     — rendered outcome_join.sql.j2 block
    feature_join_cte     — rendered feature_join.sql.j2 block
#}
